What you need to know:

Kandie, the world record holder over the distance, set a new course record of 59:33 to beat compatriot Geoffrey Kamworor in an exciting battleKandie ran a tactical race sticking with the pack of five athletes before increasing his pace after crossing the 18km markKamworor, who was taking part in his first international race since he recovered from a motorbike accident in Eldoret last year, settled second in 59:37